[[File:Banta_Four.jpg|thumb|A Banta Four spacecraft]]
A '''Banta Four''' was a silver-colored single-[[Pilot/Legends|pilot]] [[Starfighter/Legends|starfighter]] with room for at least one passenger, used by the [[Knights of Sith|Knights of the Sith]]. It had a small cockpit and large engines, which could kick up dust when warming up. A hatch was set into the side, and the power could be controlled remotely.

A Banta Four traveled over to the [[Fourth Moon of Utapau]], soaring over the atmosphere. [[Annikin Starkiller]], the eldest son of the Starkiller family, a family of Jedi-Bendu exiles in hiding from the Knights of the Sith, had witnessed its arrival while on patrol and warned his father, [[Kane Starkiller]], and younger brother, [[Deak Starkiller]] of its arrival. Upon explaining that only one arrived, Kane figured they won't need to fix their transport.

After Kane killed a [[Unidentified Knight of the Sith|Sith]], he and his surviving son, Annikin, took their opponent's Banta Four to the [[Aquilaean system]].

==Behind the scenes==
As part of the bevy of name changes introduced in the [[The Star Wars first draft|first draft]], Banta Fours were renamed "Cao" Fours.

The Banta Four, with the addition of an h, became [[Bantha/Legends|Bantha]], an entirely different type of transport. [[Bantha/Legends|Banthas]] first appeared (as creatures) in a brief aside in the [[Adventures of the Starkiller, Episode I: The Star Wars|second draft]].

"Banta" was also the designation of a [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Rebel]] flight group that attacked the [[DS-1 Orbital Battle Station/Legends|Death Star]] in the second draft.

